owner: WA Department of Biodiversity, Conservation and Attractions (DBCA)
model: YDOC, Humidity/Temp HMP110+, Wind WMS301, Solar Rad SR05-D1A3-BL, Raingauge Rimco 7499.
comments:
A new weather station was installed on 8 Sept 2021. The previous weather station (since August 2017) was a Vaisala WXT 536 multi-weather probe head (for Air-Temp, Humidity and Wind) mounted on a 10 tower. A Rimco 7499 rain gauge was installed 31 Oct 2018.
A Rimco 7499 rain gauge was installed on 31 Oct 2018, so from this date the station is now reporting rainfall using this gauge. This rain gauge is at a standard height rather than up the 10m tower (like all the other probes).
